g.aria-label: Your contract should not allow everyone to spend the coins sent to it.
Contracts that do not verify signatures are spendable by transactions that can be easily replayable by third parties, which may lead to a double spend situation or even theft of your coins.
These operators pull or push data from or to the execution stack, either transforming the data or not.
These stack operators cause the whole contract to fail if they fail internally for whatever reason.
These operators evaluate the topmost item from the stack and causes execution to continue through different branches accordingly.
These are values taken by operators.
